# 5. Write a Python program that takes two inputs from the user:
# A sentence
# A filename
# Then perform the following operations:
# i. Check whether the sentence starts with "Hello".
# ii. Convert the sentence into a list of words.
# iii. Find the position of the word "Python" in the sentence
# iv. Join the list of words back into a single sentence separated by spaces.
# v. Take another input string and check whether it contains only alphabetic characters.
# vi. Check whether the filename ends with .txt.


# Sentence: Hello I am learning Python programming
# Filename: notes.txt

user_input1 = input("Write a one line sentence: ")
user_input2 = input("Write a Filename: ")

print("\n")

print("Starts with Hello: ", user_input1.startswith("Hello"))
print("Sentence into List: ", user_input1.split(","))
print("Position of words Python:", user_input1.find("Python"))
list_into_string = user_input1.split(",")
print("Splitted List Into String:", "".join(list_into_string))

print("\n")

print("Starts with Hello: ", user_input1.isalpha())
